<CSSScrollbar-width>
<summary>
The <strong><c>scrollbar-width</c></strong> property allows the author to set the maximum thickness of an element&amp;apos;s scrollbars when they are shown.
</summary>
<remarks>
<para>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/CSS_overflow">CSS overflow</see> module<br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/CSS_scrollbars_styling">CSS scrollbars styling</see> module<br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/overflow">overflow</see><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/scrollbar-gutter">scrollbar-gutter</see><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/scrollbar-color">scrollbar-color</see><br/></para>
<para><seealso href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/scrollbar-width"> <em>See also on MDN</em> </seealso></para>
</remarks>
<value><blockquote class="NOTE"><h5>NOTE</h5><strong>Note:</strong> User Agents must apply any <c>scrollbar-width</c> value set on the root element to the viewport.</blockquote></value>
</CSSScrollbar-width>
